CAPE TOWN - The controversial proposed sugar tax will be discussed on Tuesday.Parliament s Finance Committee is expected to hold its first round of public hearings on the matter. During his budget speech last year, Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan announced a sugar tax would be levied in April 2017.READ: #Budget2016: Government to tax sugary drinksIt's part of the state's efforts to curb the high obesity rate.The health sector has welcomed the idea, saying it will be a step in the right direction for South Africa.But lobby groups object, saying it will add further pressure to an industry already suffering the effects of drought.eNCA